s origin is unknown, but doctors writing in the Medical Journal of Australia, speculate  it may come from the environment, soil or could even be carried by mosquitoes." "The World Health organization says early detection and antibiotic treatment are key to dealing with Buruli ulcer.""The disease is commonly treated with a different combination of antibiotics, and where necessary, surgical techniques such as skin grafting."SOURCES: Medical Journal of Australia, World Health Organization, BBChttps://www.mja.com.au/journal/2018/208/7/tackling-worsening-epidemic-buruli-ulcer-australia-information-void-time-urgenthttp://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs199/en/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-australia-43779187***]]></description>
